Value.value: A giant with a warm heart.
Hail! Hope you enjoy your stay here. We are growing again!
.. Say, do you maybe have a moment to assist me?
See, I'm ever on duty it seems, but I heard the shrine of Chauntea has lovely pink flowers!
Now, there is this girl I'm seeing and her favorite color is... well, pink. So I want to give her one of those flowers.
So could you get one for me? It's just north of here, and I would be very grateful if you could!
Have you got the flower yet? You can find them at the Shrine of Chauntea just north of here.
Thank you again! She loved the flower so much that she wants more of them *laughs*
Is that it? It sure is lovely! Thank you so much. Here! *hands over a small bag of coin*

Eye of Irony Keadilan is typical of an acolyte of Hoar.  His ceremonial attire consists of a black tunic over a long gray robe, with gloves of soft black leather. Around his waist, he wears a dark-red sash with silver borders; he doesn't have trophies or tokens of past victories attached to it at this time. He wears an amulet that displays the holy symbol of Hoar and serves as the focus for his cleric's powers. Finally, he always carries a curved dagger.

Value.value: Welcome to the Shrine of Hoar, the Doombringer. May you always experience poetic justice.
Why am I carrying my dagger?  I always carry my dagger.
Allowances? Excuses set forth to falsely acquit the condemned. Allowances exploit, pervert, and impede the course of justice.
Violence repays violence. Evil repays evil. Good repays good. These are the tenets of Hoar, who brings justice and retribution to each according to their actions.
